A recursive function calls itself until a base case is met. Here's a simple calculator that can add any number of inputs using just one line of code. Just click "Run" and think about it:
```
function add(x, s = 0) {
  console.log(x > 0? add(x - 1, s + x) : s);
}
add(5, 0); // Outputs 15
```
